## Commit humanizer

Before a commit is done, check it passes `isCommitedPassedHumanizer`:
does the message read like a person wrote it — plain, specific — or
does it read AI-templated (corporate "Add X and fix Y" headline,
bullet-listy body, boilerplate trailers)? If it fails, reformat it.

- **Keep it short**: title only is the default. No multi-paragraph
  explanation body unless the user asks for more detail.
- **Title style — Adjective Noun**: short title, `Adjective Noun` form
  (e.g. "Proper Icon", "Sharper Sizing"), not a verb-first changelog line
  ("Fix X", "Add Y").
- **Caveman line (opt-in only)**: only add a `Caveman: ...` line if the
  user asks for it — not by default.
- Drop `Co-Authored-By: <AI tool>` trailers by default; only include one
  if explicitly requested for that commit.
- If the commit hasn't been pushed yet, amend it rather than leaving a
  bad message in history. If it has been pushed, ask before rewriting
  (needs a force-push).

Full rule + rationale: `AGENTS.md` in pgi-web-app-workspace repo root.
